---
description: Database rules
globs: database/**
---

Use PostgreSQL.

Keep schema in `database/schema.sql`.

Keep example and imported data in `database/seed.sql`.

The local database should store only:
- light_points
- admins
- integration_logs
- optional technical configuration / field mappings

The local database must not store:
- citizen phone numbers
- citizen e-mails
- citizen identity
- report text
- uploaded photos
- full local report lifecycle
- repair statuses
- technician assignments
- report history as an authoritative system

Street light data should include fields such as:
- id
- inventory_number
- latitude
- longitude
- address (geocoded from coordinates once, stored in DB — not recomputed on each request)
- address_geocoded_at
- type
- power_w, if available
- installation_year, if available
- status
- note
- created_at
- updated_at

Import requirements:
- support CSV, JSON or GeoJSON if implemented
- validate inventory number, coordinates and duplicates
- invalid rows must produce understandable errors
- import must not overwrite existing data without confirmation

Export requirements:
- support CSV or JSON if implemented
